<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<html xmlns:MadCap="http://www.madcapsoftware.com/Schemas/MadCap.xsd">
    <body>
        <li>To specify a consumer that the application receives events from, perform these steps:<ol style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;"><li>In the <b>Event Flows</b> section, select <b>Consumers</b>.</li><li>Click <b>Add Consumer</b>.</li><li>Type a <b>Name</b> for the consumer.</li><li style="font-weight: normal;">Select a consumer type. The options available depend on the selected <b>Broker Type</b>.</li><li><p>To add a topic subscription to the consumer, click <b>Add Subscription</b> and enter the topic address for the consumer to subscribe to.</p><p>You can use <code>*</code> and <code>&gt;</code> as wildcard characters to subscribe to a group of related topics. For more information, see <MadCap:xref href="../../../../Cloud/Event-Portal/event-portal-topic-addresses.htm#Topic_Subscriptions">Topic Subscriptions</MadCap:xref>. When you enter a topic subscription, a <b>Preview of Attracted Events</b> shows all  event versions  with a matching topic address that are published by an application version that has been added to at least one modeled event mesh. You can add more than one subscription to a consumer. </p></li><li>(Optional) If you set the <b>Type</b> to <b>Solace Event Queue</b>, click <b>Set Configuration</b> to include configuration details for the queue. For more information, see <MadCap:xref href="../../../../Cloud/Event-Portal/event-portal-runtime-config.htm" target="_blank">Configuring Event Brokers from Setting Queue Configurations in [%=Product-Names.eventportal_product_short%]</MadCap:xref>.<ul><li>You can update the default configuration settings with information about the queue on the event broker.</li><li>For ease of management, you may want to use the same name for the consumer in the application and the queue it represents on the event broker.</li><li>After you set the configuration, clicking <b>Reset to Default</b> removes any customizations.</li></ul></li><li>Repeat steps b to f for every consumer that you want to add.</li></ol></li>
    </body>
</html>